Students will be given the main principles of  how to develop inquiry-based science workshops that strengthen critical thinking skills and challenge students to participate. Students will prepare 2-4 workshops and elaborate them in seminars. In the final part of the course the workshops will be piloted in schools.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to provide students with basic understanding and practical skills in  how to prepare motivating and encouraging  science workshops for primary and secondary school students.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of this course student: 1. Is familiar with main principles of  how to develop motivating,  inquiry-based science workshops 2. Has skills to use experimental equipment in science workshops 3. Has a general knowledge of science topics in National Curriculum 4. Follows necessary safety rules in science workshops
